    Playwright handles new windows using the page.waitForEvent('popup') or context.waitForEvent('page').
    const [newPage] = await Promise.all([
      context.waitForEvent('page'),
      page.click('text=Open Window')
    ]);

    await newPage.waitForLoadState();
    console.log(await newPage.title());

Q: How do you handle JavaScript alerts in Playwright?
    Playwright listens to the dialog event.
    page.on('dialog', async dialog => {
      console.log(dialog.message());
      await dialog.accept();
    });

    await page.click('#alertButton');

Q: How do you handle popup windows?
    const popupPromise = page.waitForEvent('popup');
    await page.click('#openPopup');
    const popup = await popupPromise;

    await popup.waitForLoadState();

Q: How does Playwright support parallel execution?
    Playwright runs tests in parallel using workers.
    Configuration in playwright.config.js:
    module.exports = {
      workers: 4
    };
    npx playwright test --workers=4

Q Excel Reading
    Playwright does not have built-in Excel support. We use libraries like:
    xlsx
    exceljs
    const XLSX = require('xlsx');

    const workbook = XLSX.readFile('data.xlsx');
    const sheet = workbook.Sheets['Sheet1'];

    const data = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(sheet);

    console.log(data);

Q Excel Writing
    const XLSX = require('xlsx');

    const data = [
     {name: "John", age: 30}
    ];

    const worksheet = XLSX.utils.json_to_sheet(data);
    const workbook = XLSX.utils.book_new();

    XLSX.utils.book_append_sheet(workbook, worksheet, "Sheet1");

    XLSX.writeFile(workbook, "output.xlsx");

